snippet.textDisplay: I love fury, ex boxer myself, and i struggle daily with mental health, his story is arguablly the greatest comeback of an athlete of all time, awe inspiring really, but........beating wlad and deontay wilder are steps on the path to becoming an all time great, he's well on his way, not quite there in terms of his record, but he will be if he keeps adding quality names to his resume, i'd love to see him beat AJ, dillian whyte, joseph parker ect, to cement his legacy, and while i do think deontay wilder is an exceptional puncher, he's a terrible boxer, who was fed bums, ortiz aside, who is a dinosaur in terms in age in boxing and so far past his prime, imo deontays not the hardest hitting heavyweight ever, that belongs to ernie shavers, wilders mix of speed and power is what makes his shots so dangerous, and his amatuer technique adds to the danger, as his punches come up from his arse, can't wait to see tysons next step in his journey, i pray he keeps it all together as he's a good man with a big heart, and mad as a hatter in a lovable way.
